Description: Fragment from body of a Chian pottery transport amphora; dark brown lines on a thick light slip; brush stokes visible. Hard, slightly porous, reddish/brown clay, between Munsell 2.5YR 6/4 (light reddish brown) and 7.5YR 6/3 (light brown); white and yellow inclusions.
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 323)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.115, p.225, pl.67)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
